author: COMSOL
description: This example utilizes a low-power 35Â GHz Ka-band millimeter wave and its reflectivity to moisture for noninvasive cancer diagnosis. Since skin tumors contain more moisture than healthy skin, it leads to stronger reflections on this frequency band. Hence the probe detects abnormalities in terms of S-parameters at the tumor locations. Temperature variation of the skin and fraction of necrotic tissue analyses are performed as well.
